The paper deals with the adaptation of the BitTorrent protocol for multimedia on-demand streaming systems, which involves modifications to its core algorithms. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including networked systems (cs.NI), multimedia (cs.MM), distributed computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and systems and control (cs.SY). Given the focus on peer selection policies, cs.NI and cs.MM are the most likely categories, followed by cs.DC and cs.DS, while cs.SY is less likely but still possible.
